cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE

The paper proposes a method for detecting anomalies in business processes using autoencoders, which is a machine learning technique commonly used in the field of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with fraud detection, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses event logs, which are commonly used in the field of databases, suggesting the category cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves analyzing the detected anomalies, which requires some level of artificial intelligence, suggesting the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with business processes, which is a topic commonly studied in the field of software engineering, suggesting the category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
